org.tikv.common.columnar

Class TiColumnVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tikv.common.columnar.TiColumnVector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BatchedTiChunkColumnVector, TiBlockColumnVector, TiChunkColumnVector, TiRowColumnVector

    public abstract class TiColumnVector
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    An interface is mostly copied from Spark's ColumnVector (we do not link it here because we do not want to pollute tikv java client's dependencies).

    Most of the APIs take the rowId as a parameter. This is the batch local 0-based row id for values in this TiColumnVector.

    Spark only calls specific `get` method according to the data type of this TiColumnVector, e.g. if it's int type, Spark is guaranteed to only call getInt(int) or getInts(int, int).

    TiColumnVector is expected to be reused during the entire data loading process, to avoid allocating memory again and again.

      • close

        public abstract void close()
        Cleans up memory for this column vector. The column vector is not usable after this.

        This overwrites `AutoCloseable.close` to remove the `throws` clause, as column vector is in-memory and we don't expect any exception to happen during closing.

        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
